('proj-ml-capstone', 'ph-capstone', 101, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project', 'Capstone project: Build an end-to-end ML project with data pipeline, model training, evaluation, deployment, monitoring plan, documentation, and portfolio presentation.', 'side', 16, 'advanced', '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Build an end-to-end ML project with data pipeline, model training, evaluation, deployment, monitoring plan, documentation, and portfolio presentation.","projectKind":"portfolio_capstone","projectScope":"portfolio_capstone","projectPurpose":"Integrate several roadmap areas into a portfolio-ready case study.","phaseContext":"Portfolio, Production Readiness, and Capstone","deliverable":"a portfolio-ready Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact","skillsToPractice":["Technical Case Studies","Model Evaluation","Python","Feature Engineering","Portfolio Communication"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: model behavior and evaluation, pipeline stages, monitoring signals.","Choose a coherent product or case-study scenario that can integrate the strongest projects from the roadmap.","Define the architecture, data or workflow model, user path, and review evidence before implementation.","Build the core artifact end-to-end with scoped features rather than disconnected demos.","Add validation evidence appropriate to the role, such as tests, metrics, query checks, playtest notes, traces, screenshots, or incident notes.","Prepare a case study explaining decisions, trade-offs, limitations, and what would need further review for real deployment.","Package the repository or artifact so another person can reproduce or inspect the result.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"expectedEvidence":["a portfolio-ready Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Case study page or write-up that connects the artifact to role-relevant decisions and evidence.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement.","Architecture, review checklist, and limitation section suitable for portfolio discussion."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":false,"milestone":true,"source":"roadmap.sh/machine-learning","nodeKey":"proj-ml-capstone"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Technical Case Studies, Model Evaluation, Python through a focused Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a portfolio-ready Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact is available for review.","The Machine Learning Engineer Capstone Project scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb),
('proj-open-source-ml-contribution', 'ph-capstone', 102, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Open Source ML Contribution', 'Optional practice project: Contribute documentation, tests, examples, or bug fixes to an ML-related open source project.', 'side', 5, 'advanced', '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Contribute documentation, tests, examples, or bug fixes to an ML-related open source project.","projectKind":"ai_ml_application","projectScope":"small_practice_artifact","projectPurpose":"Practice the surrounding roadmap segment through a small reviewable artifact.","phaseContext":"Portfolio, Production Readiness, and Capstone","deliverable":"a working Open Source ML Contribution notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes","skillsToPractice":["Python"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Open Source ML Contribution scenario, target user or reviewer, and the specific Portfolio, Production Readiness, and Capstone concepts it will demonstrate.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"expectedEvidence":["a working Open Source ML Contribution notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Evaluation cases, model/prompt/retrieval configuration, and notes on weak or unsafe outputs.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":true,"milestone":false,"source":"roadmap.sh/machine-learning","nodeKey":"proj-open-source-ml-contribution"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Python through a focused Open Source ML Contribution artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Open Source ML Contribution notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Open Source ML Contribution scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb);
